        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1134<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Shipping
                        Administrator</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LVAES1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Land</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">and the Assistant to the <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Shipping Administrator</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MHT1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Regional Director for the Combined United
                        Kingdom and Continental Areas, <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> Shipping
                        Administration</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MT1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Monroe</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">and the Representative on the London Branch of
                        the United Maritime Executive Board</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJW1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Carnwath</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-23">23 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 221. To <persName corresp="#p_MT1">Monroe</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_CJW1">Carnwath</persName>, <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>
                    Shipping Administration, London, England. Repeat to <persName corresp="#p_CCG1">Conway</persName>, <gloss target="#t_WSA1">WSA</gloss>, Washington, D. C.
                    from <persName corresp="#p_LVAES1">Vice Admiral Land</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MHT1">Morse</persName>. Reference your <gloss target="#t_Wsa1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wsa</hi>
                    </gloss> 3844 July 21.<note n="1" xml:id="d1134fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1132">Document No. 1132</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Have discussed matter with State Department here and <persName corresp="#p_WWG1">Weston</persName>. <gloss target="#t_UMA1">UMA</gloss> papers should <hi rend="italic">not</hi> be sent to officials of former Polish Government and
                    they should <hi rend="italic">not</hi> be invited to attend meetings or
                    communicated with further on <gloss target="#t_UMA1">UMA</gloss> matters.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
